				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">IRQ counters are relatively simple, but still not very discrete chip friendly; you'd really need 6-7 chips for a decent one. If I were more confident in board making, I'd put together a CPLD based FME7 + 32K CHR RAM, seems like the ideal solution for a game I've been thinking about but it'd probably be smarter to just PowerPak prototype it.</div>

